Japanese Reactionaries Urged to Be Prudent 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 17 (KCNA) -- The ultra-right conservative forces of Japan including Acting Secretary General of the Japan Liberal Democratic Party Abe have busied themselves with their anti-DPRK campaign recently. Referring to the resumption of the DPRK-Japan inter-governmental contact, they asserted that "the government should apply economic sanctions against north Korea unless it  takes sincere approach toward the abduction issue" and instigated the "Society of Families of Abductees" and the "Society for Rescuing Abductees" to release a statement demanding the government apply economic sanctions. They went the lengths of peddling it on the international arena.
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun today observes: Lurking behind this ruckus is a sinister political purpose to incite "people's sentiment" over the abduction issue in a bid to win political clout and expand their power bases. This is also aimed to mislead the people's mindset to creating an atmosphere hostile to the DPRK in the Japanese society in an effort to scuttle the inter-governmental contact between the DPRK and Japan and torpedo the implementation of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No matter how much the Japanese reactionaries may talk about the abduction issue the DPRK does not care at all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan seems to calculate that the DPRK would find it difficult to live on without its "economic aid". This is a height of folly.
 The  Japanese ultra-right conservative forces seek to frighten the DPRK over the issue of economic sanctions and meet its political interests. This is, however, nothing but a crude way of thinking of country philistines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK does not care whether Japan applies economic sanctions against it or not. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries' oft-repeated call for the application of economic sanctions against the DPRK with a noisy hue and cry over the abduction issue would do their country nothing good. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Abe and other political philistines of Japan, seized with their unlimited political greed, keep going reckless without properly understanding who their rival is, they will have to pay a high price for their behavior.

Joint Celebration Meeting Held in Nepal 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 17 (KCNA) -- A joint meeting of political parties of Nepal took place at the building of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist) on Oct. 8 in celebration of the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Present at the meeting were leading officials of the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist), the Nepal Communist Party (United Marxist-Leninist), and other progressive political parties and social organizations and people from all walks of life. The DPRK ambassador to Nepal and embassy officials were present on invitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist) in his speech said that the WPK's foundation and 60 year-long proud history are the history of struggle and victory unprecedented in the history of world politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foundation of the WPK meant the start of the cause of independence worldwide and its 6 decades are the history of victory of the global cause of independence, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We highly appreciate the WPK once again for its outstanding role in carrying on the Korean revolution and the global cause of independence and its historic significance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No other party than the WPK has performed so great exploits in so short span of time under very hard conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That is why the progressive political parties of the world are learning from the Juche idea and the experience of the WPK in struggle.
 The WPK is now demonstrating its might all over the world as a vanguard to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, reunify the country independently and peacefully under the wise Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il and accomplish the cause of independence against imperialism on a world-wide scale. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (United Marxist-Leninist) in his speech said that the Korean revolution began with arms and the WPK, an ever-victorious party, was founded on the basis of the arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il is based on the uniqueness of the Korean revolution, he said.

Proposal for Founding DFRK Supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 17 (KCNA) -- Juda Tsootetsi, chairman of the South African Association for Friendship and Solidarity with Korean People, issued a statement on Oct. 5 on the occasion of the 25th anniversary of the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo.
 President Kim Il Sung set forth the proposal for founding the DFRK as the most realistic and rational way of preventing the national division and achieving the reunification of the country at an early date, the statement said, and went on:
 The proposal is a great programme for the reunification of Korea as it clarifies the whole picture of a reunified state and the specific ways of realizing it. It is the most fair and rational one acceptable to anyone desirous of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should not interfere in the internal affairs of the Koreans any longer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should immediately stop its moves to provoke a new war on the Korean Peninsula, withdraw its aggression troops from south Korea unconditionally at once and halt doing anything obstructive to the reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the Korean people under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il will surely smash the outside forces' interference and obstructions and achieve the national reunification, we once again extend full support to them in their struggle for the independent and peaceful reunification of the country.

RS. on Tradition of DIU 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 17 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Monday devotes an article to the 23rd anniversary of the publication of the famous work of leader Kim Jong Il "The Workers' Party of Korea Is a Juche-Type Revolutionary Party Which Inherited the Glorious Tradition of the DIU" on Oct. 17, Juche 71 (1982).
 Kim Jong Il in his work clarified great historical significance of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union (DIU) in the history of the Workers' Party of Korea and the revolutionary struggle. On this basis he profoundly and comprehensively elucidated precious success and experience established in the course of the struggle for founding and building a Juche-type revolutionary party and clearly indicated the way for accomplishing the cause of party building which started from the DIU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sagacity of the leadership of Kim Jong Il who has resolutely carried forward the tradition of the DIU lies in holding fast to the banner of independence in all fields of party building and activities and directing greatest efforts always to strengthening the unity of the party ranks, a signed article of the daily says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has wisely led the WPK to thoroughly apply the principle of independence put forward by the DIU in all fields of party building and activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is one of the greatest exploits performed by the DIU that it made a new history of the unity of the revolutionary ranks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unity of the Party is based on the steadfast revolutionary faith and obligation to devotedly defend Kim Jong Il and based on the great Juche idea and Songun idea. The whole party acts as one under his monolithic leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is his wisdom that he has steadily strengthened the close kindred relations between the party and the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As he leads the Party, it will display its pride as a patriotic party opening a heyday of national prosperity and an ever-victorious revolutionary party leading the era of independence.

RS. Calls for Accelerating General March of Songun Revolution 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 17 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Monday editorially calls upon all party members, servicepersons of the People's Army and people to more powerfully accelerate the general march of Songun revolution in high spirit, keeping in mind the present glory and happiness that they grandly celebrated the 60th birthday of the glorious Workers' Party of Korea in the presence of leader Kim Jong Il, a peerlessly great man.
 They should demonstrate to the full in the present general march their firm faith and will to carry out revolution to the end, holding fast to his Songun idea and leadership as their lifeline, the editorial says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should uphold his Songun revolutionary leadership with loyalty, taking the pledge of faith made at the grand October festival as a motto of life and struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should hold high the slogan calling for uniting close around the headquarters of revolution, the heart of Korea and a symbol of invincibility. We should become hot-blooded comrades of Songun revolution who take it as pure conscience and obligation to devotedly defend the headquarters of revolution and share life and death with him to the end. It is imperative to develop the unity of the army and people in idea and struggle on to a new high stage in conformity with the requirement of the Songun era. We should give full play to the revolutionary comradeship and the spirit of collectivism to keep in fuller bloom our social traits of helping and leading each other forward and living in harmony as a big family. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the WPK serve as a program of struggle and militant banner our army and people should consistently hold high in the present general march. We should keep the enthusiasm and stamina with which we celebrated the October holiday with productive surge at all socialist construction sites where a powerful drive to implement the joint slogans is prevailing.
 No force in the world can stand in the way of our army and people who are emerging victorious with indomitable faith and heroic struggle under the leadership of the great Party, stresses the editorial.

International Commodity Exhibition to Be Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 17 (KCNA) -- The First Autumn International Commodity Exhibition will be held in Pyongyang from October 24 to 27 under the sponsorship of the Korean International Exhibition Corporation.
 The exhibition will be participated in by foreign enterprises from Europe, Asia and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display there will be equipment for developing latest technologies and various kinds of ironware, machine tools, poultry facilities, medicines, agricultural chemicals and fertilizers, petrol chemical goods, electric and electronic goods, foodstuffs and daily necessities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the exhibition trade consultations and exchanges will be conducted and joint venture and economic cooperation between enterprises discussed.
 More than 80 companies and enterprises in China, Romania, Malaysia, Thailand, Japan, Taiwan, Italy and Sweden have applied for the participation and have been registered. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of applicants continues to increase. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean International Exhibition Corporation organizes the international commodity show in each May and October in order to promote cooperation and trade activities.

Three Forms of Cooperation Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 17 (KCNA) -- Three forms of cooperation for national independence, peace against war and reunification and patriotism guarantee independent reunification and national prosperity. They are in full line with the desire of the compatriots for achieving the reunification of the country through the great unity of the nation free from foreign interference as they provide basic ways of conducting the movement for independence and reunification on the fundamental principles of national reunification.
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. It continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said three forms of cooperation reflect the unanimous desire and fixed will of all Koreans to live and develop independently, promote the process of national reconciliation and reunification and defend peace of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foreign forces are alien ones and the forces for division. What the foreign forces have done since their occupation of a half of Korea is nothing but acts against the reconciliation and unity of the nation, peace and peaceful reunification. It is due to the foreign forces that the Korean nation still remains divided and has undergone misfortune and pain and a tense situation is prevailing on the Korean Peninsula and it is exposed to the danger of a new war.
 Even at this time the U.S. imperialists are running amuck to provoke a new war, chilling the desire of the Koreans for reconciliation and unity and persisting in their moves against the north in a bid to block independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three forms of cooperation provide the only way of smashing the moves of the U.S. imperialists and achieving independent reunification. This cooperation is effective enough to frustrate the foreign forces' moves to provoke a new war, nuclear war and create a peaceful environment for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans in the north, the south and overseas should wage a more dynamic struggle to realize the three forms of cooperation under the banner of "By our nation itself" whose vitality has been fully demonstrated in practice, as required by the developing reality.
